# Amazon NFT — European Fulfillment Network Analysis

## Full Data Dictionary

---

## 1. Dataset Overview

This dataset represents a **multi-echelon European fulfillment network**, capturing the full supply chain from **suppliers to customers** over a **4-month period (Sep–Dec 2024)**.

| Table                    | Rows   | Time Period      | Purpose                 |
| ------------------------ | ------ | ---------------- | ----------------------- |
| suppliers                | 10     | Static           | Vendor master data      |
| nodes                    | 24     | Static           | Network location master |
| skus                     | 250    | Static           | Product catalogue       |
| purchase_orders          | 125    | Sep–Dec 2024     | Supplier replenishment  |
| inventory                | 1,312  | Current snapshot | Stock levels            |
| transfers                | 2,860  | Sep–Dec 2024     | Shipment movements      |
| replenishment_comparison | 4,849  | Sep–Dec 2024     | Push vs Pull simulation |
| orders                   | 16,615 | Nov–Dec 2024     | Customer demand         |
| sla_performance          | 1,280  | Sep–Dec 2024     | Transit performance     |

**Total:** 27,325 rows across 9 tables

---

## 2. Table Definitions

### 2.1 suppliers

**Purpose:** Vendor master data — origin of supply chain

| Column            | Type    | Description                 |
| ----------------- | ------- | --------------------------- |
| supplier_id       | VARCHAR | Unique supplier ID          |
| supplier_name     | VARCHAR | Supplier name               |
| location          | VARCHAR | Supplier location           |
| lead_time_days    | INT     | PO to delivery time         |
| reliability_score | DECIMAL | On-time delivery rate (0–1) |

**Relationships:**

* Linked to **nodes** via `primary_supplier_id`
* Linked to **purchase_orders** via `supplier_id`

---

### 2.2 nodes

**Purpose:** Defines all physical locations in the network

| Column              | Type    | Description         |
| ------------------- | ------- | ------------------- |
| node_id             | VARCHAR | Unique node ID      |
| node_type           | VARCHAR | Node classification |
| location            | VARCHAR | Geographic location |
| capacity_units      | INT     | Storage capacity    |
| primary_supplier_id | VARCHAR | Default supplier    |

**Node Types**

| Type  | Role                      | Replenishment |
| ----- | ------------------------- | ------------- |
| 1DC   | Primary DC (bulk storage) | Daily         |
| RDC   | Regional buffer           | Weekly        |
| IXD   | Cross-dock (no storage)   | Continuous    |
| FC    | Fulfillment center        | On demand     |
| NEXUS | Last-mile hub             | Daily         |

**Relationships:** Central table linked to all operational tables

---

### 2.3 skus

**Purpose:** Product catalogue with demand characteristics

| Column         | Type    | Description         |
| -------------- | ------- | ------------------- |
| sku_id         | VARCHAR | Product ID          |
| category       | VARCHAR | Product category    |
| velocity       | VARCHAR | Demand speed        |
| unit_cost_eur  | DECIMAL | Unit cost           |
| weight_kg      | DECIMAL | Product weight      |
| demand_profile | VARCHAR | Seasonality pattern |
| supplier_id    | VARCHAR | Supplier            |

**Velocity Definitions**

| Velocity | Meaning        | Priority |
| -------- | -------------- | -------- |
| fast     | Daily demand   | High     |
| medium   | Weekly demand  | Medium   |
| slow     | Monthly demand | Low      |

**Demand Profiles:** flat, winter_peak, summer_peak, event_driven

